{"repository": {"pullRequest": {"number": 2913, "title": "use approximated S_abs", "body": "Fixes #2911 \r\n\r\nThe current way to compute the absolute overlap is only exact for uncontracted, cartesian basis functions.\r\nAs soon as one uses contracted cartesians or uses spherical harmonics it is necessary to transform the overlap matrix from the primitives.\r\n\r\nThis can be done only in an approximated way using the RHS of the triangle inequality:\r\n\r\n```math\r\n\\int |\\phi_i(\\mathbf{r})| \\, |\\phi_j(\\mathbf{r})| \\, d\\mathbf{r}\r\n\\leq\r\n\\sum_{\\alpha,\\beta} |c_{\\alpha i}| \\, |c_{\\beta j}| \\int |\\chi_\\alpha(\\mathbf{r})| \\, |\\chi_\\beta(\\mathbf{r})| \\, d\\mathbf{r}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nIn this PR it is ensured that:\r\n1. all transformation matrices are indeed positive (fixing #2911)\r\n2. one can also use spherical harmonics.\r\n\r\nSince this is now only an approximated S_abs, the function is named accordingly.", "baseRefName": "master", "baseRefOid": "68146a61d9463619865a15bc394817eb88bcb13d", "baseRepository": {"nameWithOwner": "pyscf/pyscf"}, "url": "https://github.com/pyscf/pyscf/pull/2913", "createdAt": "2025-07-28T18:01:26Z", "mergedAt": "2025-08-11T16:16:21Z"}}, "base": {"repo": {"full_name": "pyscf/pyscf"}, "sha": "68146a61d9463619865a15bc394817eb88bcb13d"}, "diff_url": "https://github.com/pyscf/pyscf/pull/2913.diff", "number": 2913, "created_at": "2025-07-28T18:01:26Z", "merged_at": "2025-08-11T16:16:21Z", "resolved_issues": [2911]}
