{"repository": {"pullRequest": {"number": 3150, "title": "Fix mo_coeff reshape size in pbc/scf/hf DF JK", "body": "This fixes #3149.\r\n\r\nSummary: For PBC calculations, when DF is used and memory isn't enough to store ERIs, the initial SCF cycle can fail due to the non-square shape of mo_coeff produced by the minao init_guess. The fixed code is now the same logic as in the molecular DF JK [here](https://github.com/pyscf/pyscf/blob/master/pyscf/df/df_jk.py#L341). I don't even know if this mo_coeff that is tagged to dm is actually used or not.", "baseRefName": "master", "baseRefOid": "e1c6a4519f9a4b0ae0d125c74387b7c90d9437d9", "baseRepository": {"nameWithOwner": "pyscf/pyscf"}, "url": "https://github.com/pyscf/pyscf/pull/3150", "createdAt": "2026-03-04T19:45:04Z", "mergedAt": "2026-03-05T17:05:28Z"}}, "base": {"repo": {"full_name": "pyscf/pyscf"}, "sha": "e1c6a4519f9a4b0ae0d125c74387b7c90d9437d9"}, "diff_url": "https://github.com/pyscf/pyscf/pull/3150.diff", "number": 3150, "created_at": "2026-03-04T19:45:04Z", "merged_at": "2026-03-05T17:05:28Z", "resolved_issues": [3149]}
